gate: OPEN
task: S03-T1
title: Port navitrack dark theme
objective: Incorporate the military-use dark theme from the navitrack instance into kvit-tracking.

context:
- navitrack has a well-defined dark theme appropriate for military applications.
- This tasks involves extracting those CSS values/theme configurations and applying them to the kvit-tracking Tailwind or CSS configuration.

steps:
1. Locate the dark theme colors in the `navitrack` instance.
2. Port those color variables into `kvit-tracking` (`tailwind.config.js` or `index.css`).
3. Ensure the base layout and primary components fall back or actively use these dark theme colors.

acceptance-criteria:
- [x] kvit-tracking successfully uses the military dark theme colors originating from navitrack.
- [x] Global background and text contrast adhere to proper design rules under the new theme.
